        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 7:30AM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 730 AM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from near Molena to Big Lazer Creek Wma to near Juniper,
and moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Thomaston, Barnesville, Butler, Roberta, Talbotton, Manchester,
Woodbury, Woodland, Molena, Yatesville, Junction City, Culloden,
Geneva, Sunset Village, Lincoln Park, The Rock, Upatoi, Juniper,
Atwater, and Baughville.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
